queries: This sign can also be made with a more relaxed handshape on the dominant hand (e.g., the Eight handshape) and/or with the sign beginning with the middle fingertip on the lips.
verblex: 1. To turn over a page or the pages of a book or magazine.
2. To turn over the pages of a book or magazine in order to have a quick glance at the contents. English = skim, flick through, browse.
nomlex: 1. One side of one of the pieces of paper in a book, magazine, or newspaper. English = page.
2. The pieces of paper that a book, magazine, or newspaper consist of. English = page.
